node.title: NSW Omicron infections grow, source of 'mystery' cluster traced to Nigeria
node.description: Health authorities in NSW announce six new Omicron COVID-19 infections, taking the state's total number of cases to 31.
node.content: ["Health authorities in NSW have announced six new Omicron COVID-19 infections in the 24 hours to 8pm yesterday.", "It brings the total number of Omicron cases in the state to 31.\u00a0", "None have been admitted to hospital.", "The variant was first identified in southern Africa and non-Australian citizens from eight countries there have been banned from travelling Down Under.", "Twenty of the Omicron cases are linked to a cluster at Regents Park Christian School, Chanel Catholic Primary School in Regents Park and the Sydney Indoor Climbing Gym in Villawood.", "The initial\u00a0case, a student, was reported last week and was recognised as the first community transmission of the Omicron variant in Australia.", "They had not been overseas or knowingly had contact with anyone who had been abroad.", "NSW Health says the source of this cluster is believed to be a returned overseas traveller who spent time in Nigeria.", "A total of 260 new COVID-19 infections were recorded in the 24 hours to 8:00pm yesterday.", "There are a total of 155 COVID-19 patients in the state's hospitals, with 28 in intensive care.", "Five people are on ventilators.", "There were 58,706 COVID-19 tests in the reporting period.", "More to come."]
